            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>An unknown reader clipped articles from the <emph render="italic">Springfield (Mass.) Republican</emph> and, possibly, from a few other papers, from Jan. 12, 1854, to June 30, 1856, but mainly in 1856. Most of the clippings relate to emigration to Kansas and the ensuing civil war there. A scattering of other topics are also covered: the Crimean War, weather and storms, murders, election results, California gold and crime, Sen. Preston Brooks&#039;s attack on Sen. Charles Sumner, and the early days of the Fremont campaign for the presidency.</p>
                                 <p>The compiler pasted these clippings onto 39 leaves of <emph render="italic">Illinois in 1837</emph> (Philadelphia: S. Augustus Mitchell, 1837). The cover, title page, and copyright page of that volume were left unobscured.</p>
                                 <p>The Library acquired this scrapbook in 1927.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


